meta.content: 'Together the school district and the community will be committed to understanding each student's interests, needs, and ambitions in order to prepare all students for graduation with knowledge,character and the ability to lead successful lives.'

div.p: The District has set up a hotline as well as an email account as a way for families to ask questions that they may have and provide effective communication and clarity moving forward. Calls will be directed to an administrative voicemail and will be answered as routinely as possible.

div.div: The Governor issued a new Executive Order that requires schools to remain closed through May 15th. Superintendent Kopp has published an updated Continuity of Learning Plan as we continue to navigate the extended closure. The Plan is posted on our COVID-19 Page.

div.strong: Updates will be posted on our COVID-19 Page which is now listed under the Student, Parent, and Community Resources tab at the top of our Website.
